### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### STUDY MATERIAL (Documents)
### Base: {{baseUrl}}/documents
###
### Upload accepts: PDF, DOCX, DOC, TXT, PPT, PPTX, XLS, XLSX
### Files are saved to ./uploads on the server filesystem
### Text is extracted with Apache Tika
### Claude categorises and tags (if CLAUDE_API_KEY is set)
### Chunks are embedded with Voyage AI (if VOYAGE_API_KEY is set)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────


### List all documents
GET {{baseUrl}}/documents
Accept: application/json

> {%
  var docs = response.body;
  if (docs.length > 0) {
    client.global.set("documentId", docs[0].id);
    client.log("Captured documentId: " + docs[0].id);
  }
%}


###


### Get a single document by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/documents/{{documentId}}
Accept: application/json


###


### Upload a file — no account/role tag
# Change the file path to an actual file on your machine
POST {{baseUrl}}/documents
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary

--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="sample.txt"
Content-Type: text/plain

This is sample study material about SQL queries and data engineering.
BigQuery, Spark, ETL pipelines, data warehousing concepts.
--boundary--

> {%
  client.global.set("documentId", response.body.id);
  client.log("Uploaded document: " + response.body.filename + " | id: " + response.body.id);
%}


###


### Upload a file — tagged with account and role
POST {{baseUrl}}/documents?accountName=PayPal&roleName=Data%20Engineer
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary2

--boundary2
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="paypal-de-notes.txt"
Content-Type: text/plain

PayPal Data Engineering Interview Notes:
- SQL window functions
- Apache Kafka streaming
- Data pipeline design patterns
- Python pandas and PySpark
--boundary2--

> {%
  client.global.set("documentId", response.body.id);
  client.log("Uploaded tagged document: " + response.body.id);
%}


###


### Export document as PDF (download link)
GET {{baseUrl}}/documents/{{documentId}}/export?format=pdf
Accept: application/pdf


###


### Export document as DOCX (download link)
GET {{baseUrl}}/documents/{{documentId}}/export?format=docx
Accept: application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.wordprocessingml.document


###


### Delete a document
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/documents/{{documentId}}
